      <para id="id2262379">
<emphasis effect="bold">Commutativity, Associativity, and Distributivity.</emphasis> The complex numbers commute, associate, and distribute under addition and multiplication
as follows:</para>
      
      <equation id="id2262443"><m:math overflow="scroll">
<m:mtable>
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>z</m:mi>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo>+</m:mo>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>z</m:mi>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
</m:mtd>
<m:mtd>       
       <m:mo>=</m:mo>
</m:mtd>
<m:mtd>       
       <m:msub>
                <m:mi>z</m:mi>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
